The paper discusses the development of surveillance systems with human-like cognitive capabilities, which involves computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and systems and control (cs.SY). These sub-categories are all relevant to the topic of cognitive surveillance and are likely to be the most appropriate for this paper.
